I am reading this guy's book - he's like Noah Yuval Harari without the
repeatable anecdote - but I quite like the frame he uses in the article
below - talking about different kinds of democratic societies - collectivist
and individualistic - and how collectivist societies have coped with COVID
better but are not as good at innovation as individualistic societies. Think
this frame can also be extended to corporate societies - not just democratic
societies. 

 

So we are looking to build collectivist values in individualistic societies
- without removing the space that individuals need to be individuals - to
achieve the best of both worlds?

 

https://voxeu.org/article/covid-19-and-future-democracy

 

 


